    rdfs:label "Proof of Movement: Metaconceptual Art";
    la:member_of mca:collection.
mca:priority-live-auction-2009 crm:P104_is_subject_to _:b0_r10b0;
    crm:P129_is_about mca:auction-as-artwork, mca:production-live-auction-2009, mca:wtf-is-ansel-adams, mca:wtfisart;
    crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "Sun & Rain Works asserts a conceptual claim: that in 2009, in connection with the Sotheby's Photographs auction (sale N08533, New York), it designated its auction engagement — the consignment of an Ansel Adams photograph, 'San Francisco from Twin Peaks' (lot 16), together with the associated website www.wtfisart.com — as Metaconceptual Art, framed as the work The Auction as Artwork. This is the artist's own designation, made explicit over time. It is not a publicly witnessed live-creation event and has not been adjudicated as a historical fact; the Sotheby's catalogue lists the lot as an Ansel Adams photograph and does not name Sun & Rain Works. This statement makes no claim of being 'first', and does not name, compare against, or dispute any later artist or event; any such comparison would require independent recognition and separately published evidence.";
    crm:P1_is_identified_by _:b0_r10b1, _:b0_r10b2;
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300026087, aat:300435443;
    crm:P67i_is_referred_to_by _:b0_r10b3;
    crm:P94i_was_created_by _:b0_r10b4;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object;
    rdfs:label "Sun & Rain Works' conceptual claim to art at auction (2009)".
