    rdfs:label "Metaconceptual Art — WTF is Ansel Adams";
    la:access_point <https://www.metaconceptualart.com/artworks#work-wtf-is-ansel-adams>.
_:b0_r17b5 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "WTF is Ansel Adams";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300404670;
    crm:P72_has_language aat:300388277;
    a crm:E33_E41_Linguistic_Appellation.
_:b0_r17b6 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "work:wtf-is-ansel-adams";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300312355;
    a crm:E42_Identifier.
_:b0_r17b7 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "A Metaconceptual Art work that Sun & Rain Works designates around its consignment of the Ansel Adams photograph 'San Francisco from Twin Peaks' (lot 16) to Sotheby's Photographs, 2009 (sale N08533, New York). Titled as a play on the auction and the canonical name of Ansel Adams, it treats the act of bringing the photograph to auction — its lot, its authority, its attribution — as the material of a conceptual work, alongside the born-digital work www.wtfisart.com. The work is a designation asserted by the artist and made explicit over time; it is not recorded as a publicly witnessed performance, and the Sotheby's catalogue lists the lot as an Ansel Adams photograph without naming Sun & Rain Works.";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300435416;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object.
_:b0_r17b8 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "Documentation reported by Sun & Rain Works includes 2008 correspondence with Sotheby's Photographs, the public catalogue lot, photographs, and related records; these evidence the artist identity and the consignment. The fuller archive remains held by the studio pending redaction and rights review. This record asserts no historical-priority or precedence claim absent separately published evidence.";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300435416;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object.
_:b0_r18b0 a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object;
    rdfs:label "Artwork page";
    la:digitally_carried_by _:b0_r18b1.
_:b0_r18b1 <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/format> "text/html";
    a <http://www.ics.forth.gr/isl/CRMdig/D1_Digital_Object>;
    rdfs:label "Metaconceptual Art - www.wtfisart.com";
    la:access_point <https://www.metaconceptualart.com/artworks/wtfisart>.
_:b0_r18b10 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "The website was built by Sun & Rain Works around 2009 in connection with its Sotheby's Photographs auction engagement; it is not recorded as having been authored live in the auction room.";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300435416;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object.
