_:b0_r7b1 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "Evidence archive: Sun & Rain Works auction engagement (2009)";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300404670;
    crm:P72_has_language aat:300388277;
    a crm:E33_E41_Linguistic_Appellation.
_:b0_r7b2 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "record:evidence-live-auction-2009";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300312355;
    a crm:E42_Identifier.
_:b0_r7b3 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "Evidence status: mixed. Independently verifiable: (1) the public Sotheby's catalogue lot (sale N08533, lot 16) at https://www.sothebys.com/en/auctions/ecatalogue/2009/photographs-n08533/lot.16.html ; (2) a Sun and Rain Works public post carrying the 'WTF is Art' theme, dated 2013-08-29 (X post 373257603108704256), whose date is confirmed independently by the platform's timestamp-encoded ID. Held privately by the studio: the 2008-2009 correspondence, receipts, and photographs. Selected private items can be promoted to public evidence as redaction and rights review are completed.";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300435416;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object.
_:b0_r7b4 crm:P190_has_symbolic_content "The consignment engagement is corroborated by inbound 2008 correspondence from Sotheby's Photographs (confirming intake logistics and naming the department administrator) and by a shared Hana, HI mailing address linking the consignor to the Sun & Rain Works domain receipts. Contemporaneous conceptual intent is evidenced by art-referential documentation (an Andy Warhol volume juxtaposed with the photograph in images sent to Sotheby's). Each item is scoped to what it shows: these evidence identity, consignment, intent, and the concept's public continuity — not a witnessed live-creation event, and not precedence over any later artist or event.";
    crm:P2_has_type aat:300435416;
    a crm:E33_Linguistic_Object.
_:b0_r7b5 crm:P14_carried_out_by mca:sun-and-rain-works;
    crm:P4_has_time-span _:b0_r7b6;
    a crm:E65_Creation;
    rdfs:label "Compilation of the auction-engagement evidence record".
